                    {
                        "value": "Historical/Biographical Note"
                    }
                ],
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "\u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eScience \u0026 Society\u003c/span\u003e is a scholarly Marxist quarterly founded in 1936. The journal is interdisciplinary, applying a Marxist perspective to a broad range of topics; however, political economy is the most frequently represented topic, followed by Marxist philosophy, the history of communist movements, and other topics. The journal's head editor is David Laibman, a Professor Emeritus of Economics at Brooklyn College and the Graduate Center, City University of New York."
                    }
                ]
            }
